Initialize an MCPAgentSession YAML manifest for review or apply. Adapter auto-refresh usually creates sessions automatically; this command is for explicit/admin session manifests.

Usage:
  mcp-runtime access session init [name] [flags]

Flags:
      --agent-id string                Agent subject ID
      --expires-at string              Optional RFC3339 expiry timestamp
      --expires-in string              Optional relative expiry duration, for example 1h or 30m
      --force                          Replace output file if it already exists
  -h, --help                           help for init
      --human-id string                Human subject ID
      --namespace string               Manifest namespace (default "mcp-servers")
      --output string                  Output manifest path (default "session.yaml")
      --policy-version string          Policy version (default "v1")
      --revoked                        Initialize the session as revoked
      --server string                  Target MCPServer name
      --server-namespace string        Target MCPServer namespace (default: --namespace)
      --team-id string                 Team subject ID
      --trust string                   Trust level: low, medium, or high (default "low")
      --upstream-token-key string      Secret key for --upstream-token-secret (default "token")
      --upstream-token-secret string   Optional Secret name containing an upstream token

Global Flags:
      --debug      Enable debug mode with structured error logging
      --use-kube   Use direct Kubernetes mode with kubectl; requires admin/operator cluster access (admin/dev/test only)
